{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Lower the cost of British Citizenship applications to \u00a3800",
        "additional_details": "The actual administrative cost is around \u00a3575, yet applicants are charged \u00a31605. Citizenship should reflect integration and contribution, not financial privilege. Reducing the fee to \u00a3800 would be fair, transparent, and just make it easier to apply for many people.",
        "background": "We think the current cost of applying for British citizenship is disproportionately high and creates a real barrier for people who have lived, worked, and paid taxes in the UK for many years. ",
